A part of Amazon's Robotics Artificial Intelligence Organization, Canvas Technology is using spatial AI to provide end-to-end autonomous delivery of goods. By using state-of-the-art cameras and other sensors, the system perceives its surroundings with unrivaled vision and fidelity. The system combines a mix of high-performance sensors with simultaneous localization and mapping software that builds and continuously updates maps in real-time, completely automatically. It has the capability to â€˜seeâ€™ and identify different objects, people, vehicles, and places as it moves and react to moving people and vehicles in an intelligent way.
 
The Canvas team is seeking a Hardware Engineering Manager to lead our multi-disciplinary hardware engineering team in the Canvas autonomous mobile robotics team, which includes electrical, mechanical, firmware, and test engineers to develop mobile robots from concept to production and global scale. This leader will shape the structure and processes of the hardware team to deliver both rapid prototypes and production-ready units. They will collaborate closely with product management, software engineering, research science, field operations, supply chain, and safety specialties. They will execute on the existing product strategy and provide data-driven insights to own the autonomous mobile robot vision and product roadmaps. They must be able to systematically consider and clearly communicate tradeoffs between costs, resources, risks, and timelines to product teams and senior leadership.
 
 
